ethodology, which emphasizes rapid iteration and customer feedback. It allows for quick prototyping and testing of ideas, as well as the ability to pivot or change direction based on customer feedback.\n\nThe framework includes the following components:\n\n1. Minimum Viable Product (MVP): The MVP is the smallest version of a product that can be released to the market and still provide value to customers. It is designed to test the core value proposition of the product and gather feedback from early adopters.\n2. Rapid Prototyping: This involves quickly creating a basic version of the product to test its feasibility and gather feedback from potential customers. This can be done through mock", "model_ref": "general", "runner_ref": "llama.cpp", "trace": {"prompt_hash": "1c001bf40921c0aee910fb3c22ea2a1d0d2cb7b0f5668564455cde4c9b0c7035", "purpose": "default", "seed": 931431946, "n_predict": 256}}}